{
  "doc_id": "60506",
  "text": "Powder and slurries at 1-10% of castor oil plant, Ricinus communis L. (Euphorbiaceae) mixed with corn kernel killed Sitophilus oryzae L. (Coleoptera: Curculionidae) adults [CITATION_1] . In addition, leaf aqueous extract (2.5 g/20 mL) impregnated on sweet pepper foliar discs inhibited consumption of leaf discs on Anthonomus eugenii Cano (Coleoptera: Curculionidae) [CITATION_2] . Biologically active flavonoids as quercetin, quercitrin and rutin has been identified in hydroethanolic extracts of this plant (PachecoSánchez et al. 2012) .",
